metrics_conclusion: BGM1 - Bomberman (TurboGrafx-16) has higher complexity than the average song  in terms Chord Complexity and Chord Progression Novelty.
key_conclusion:
BGM1 - Bomberman (TurboGrafx-16) is written in the key of D Mixolydian.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 5th most popular key among Mixolydian keys and     the 30th most popular  among all keys. The D Mixolydian scale is similar to the D Major scale except that its 7th note (C) is a half step lower.  Mixolydian chord progressions are heavily featured in many genres of music like classic rock, which relies on the major chord built on the 7th scale degree. 

See the D Mixolydian Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Changed "ii(b5)" chord in measure 12 beat 1 to iio from Minor, and "V7(b5)/I" to simply V7(b5). It's easier and more visually appealing to borrow a chord from the parent mode instead of using accidentals to cheat it, and if something is the V7 chord of the I, **just call it V7**.
If it's V7/I, just call it V7. If it's viio7/i, borrow it from harmonic minor. Secondary chords should only be used with chords *other* than I.
